                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/3202</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-22T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 22, 10 a.m. After all American refugees shall have been taken aboard on
                    such vessels as have been ordered to Vera Cruz, if there is still room on such
                    vessels foreigners will be given refuge to whatever extent possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
